title: Kuchar leads Fiji International after 3 rounds
text:
Matt Kuchar holds 2-shot lead after 3rd round at the Fiji International THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   17, 2015 - 12:31 amLast Updated: October 17, 2015 - 12:31 am   
People: 
Oceania (160) 

SUVA, Fiji â€” American Matt Kuchar shot a three-under 69 on Saturday to maintain a two-stroke lead after three rounds of the Fiji International. 
The world No. 16 had his best round of the tournament at Natadolo Bay Golf Club to finish the third round as the only player under par at 1-under 215. 
He remained two shots ahead of Australian Aron Price who also shot 69, and they appear set to contest the title on Sunday, with Australian Nick Cullen six strokes off the lead in third. 
Local favorite Vijay Singh shot a 71 to move up to a tie for sixth, nine shots off the lead.
